So is it "safe" to update thru the Update Center?
Meaning that we can update how much we want and still be able to reset.

I make a product.  I sell a product for $X,XXX.00

I then discover that someone else made a product that tricks my product into thinking that you paid the $X,XXX.00 that I sell my product for.  I then come to find that this other product is being freely shared by peers on TPB et al.

The least I could do to keep my sales margin from being drastically deflated is adding the codes that this other product generates into the threat libraries and try to have other libraries also recognize this threat thus bringing back up my sales margin.

I'm not saying to be cautious, but recognize that you are desiring to cross the waters on a vessel.  If you you are thinking about complaining of the less then commendable service, then WALK THE FUCKIN PLANK!!!!!

Hi Robbinghood,
Didn't wanna hurt you piratemate!
I know about false positives,
I do have sandboxie
I report real bad torrents and fake uploaders on suprbay.
but
I always tought virustotal was a reliable reference. I always control unknown small sized apps there and sometimes it finds malware that wasn't detected by mine (KIS). From my own experience I know that Kaspersky somtimes recognizes it only after running it an than starts to remove the malware. (while some unknown av already recognized it)
All by all bro, we both know that we're loyal members of this community and we don't have any profit by blaming eachother.
Best regards
and keep up the good work.

I followed all the instructions:

">> When using the Kaspersky Trial Reset 2011 v3.3.1 the first time:
1. If installed, uninstall Kaspersky and restart the computer.
2. Run the KTR2011-v3.3.1, click [PURGE], and exit.
3. Install Kaspersky 2011.0.2.556 or PURE 9.1.0.124, but DO NOT activate yet!
4. Run the KTR2011-v3.3.1, click [EXTRACT], and exit. 
   >> Note: Step-4 [EXTRACT] is only required the first time! 
5. Now activate and use Kaspersky (as 30-days trial)."

[I disabled "Self-Defense"]

I get the [PURGE] button, but NOT the [EXTRACT] button. So, I never see the [RESET] button either.

However, doing the uninstall/reinstall seems to get me a "fresh" 30 days trial. But, of course, this would be a "bore" to do every 30 days!

Any ideas? I disabled "Self-Defense" when I did not see the [EXTRACT] button, but it did make any difference...
I'm doing all this on a WINXPPRO SP3 32-bit machine.

UPDATE:
1. I did the "Uninstall" process again,  BUT did not select "Complete Uninstall" [or whatever] it said. I allowed Kaspersky to retain "Application" settings and nothing else.

2. I used the resetter and got the [EXTRACT] button this time around! [yeh!]

I have Comodo Firewall/Defense+ installed also. During this above process, I cancelled Comodo until I was finished with Kaspersky. Could this have anything to do with anything?
